@page "/privacy-policy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy</PageTitle>

<h3>Privacy Policy</h3>
<p>This is the placeholder privacy policy for Yonderfix.com. Please replace this with your actual privacy policy.</p>
<p>We are committed to protecting your privacy. This site uses Bluesky authentication to access your follower data with your permission. We store access tokens and related information securely in your session to facilitate application functionality.</p>
<p>We use essential cookies for session management and authentication. By using this site, you consent to our use of these essential cookies. For more information about cookies, please see our cookie consent information, typically available via a banner or a link in the footer.</p>
<p><strong>Data Storage:</strong> Authentication tokens, DPoP keys, and your Bluesky User DID are stored in your browser's session storage. This data is cleared when you log out or when you explicitly use the "Delete My Local Data" feature.</p>
<p><strong>Data Usage:</strong> We use your access token to fetch your followers list from Bluesky and to perform actions like unfollowing users on your behalf, as initiated by you through the application's interface.</p>
<p><strong>Data Sharing:</strong> We do not share your Bluesky data or session information with any third parties.</p>
<p><strong>Data Deletion:</strong> You can clear all locally stored session data related to your account at any time by using the "Delete My Local Data" option in your account settings, which will also log you out.</p>
<p>This policy may be updated from time to time. Please check back here for the latest version.</p>
<p>Last Updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd")</p>
